## Performance Testing (JMeter)
Basic load testing was performed using Apache JMeter on the ReqRes public API.

### Test Setup
- Endpoint: GET /api/users?page=1
- Tool: Apache JMeter
- Virtual Users: 2
- Ramp-up Period: 10 seconds
- Loop Count: 2
- Constant Timer: 1000ms delay between requests

### Metrics Captured
- Response Time (Average, min and max)
- Throughput (requests per unit of time)
- Error Percentage

### Observations

- With controlled load and delays, API response was stable with 0% error rate.
- When load was increased, the API starts to fail with error 429(too many requests), indicating the rate limit on public endpoint

### Conclusions

- JMeter was was used to simulate concurrent users and analyze API behaviour under load
- The test highlights the importance of controlled environment for accurate perfomance. 

